>>> On Fri, Jul 5, 2024 at 3:05 PM Ruediger Pluem <rpluem@apache.org> wrote:
>>>>
>>>>>>>> md_crypt.c: In function 'md_cert_get_ct_scts':
>>>>>>>> md_crypt.c:2071:5: error: unknown type name 'SCT'
>>>>>>>>    SCT *sct_handle;
>>>>
>>>> This one is caused by r1918195 in >= 2.4.60. Before r1918195 OPENSSL_NO_CT was defined when openssl was < 1.1.1. Now it is not any
>>>> longer and hence md_cert_get_ct_scts gets a real function body as
>>>>
>>>> #ifndef OPENSSL_NO_CT
>>>>
>>>> (line 2068) is now true. Hence we error out on the non presence of the SCT struct (line 2071).
>>>
>>> Maybe something like the attached patch for this one too (which could
>>> avoid configure tricks for both..).
>>
>> Or rather this one.
>>
